# Oneirox: neurobiology only

For all text and code generation related to Oneirox (especially PSEO somatic pages, matrix rows, SSG templates, and copy):

## STRICTLY use
- Neurobiology and sleep physiology
- Somatic markers (body sensations tied to autonomic / motor state)
- Brain mechanics: sleep stages N1–N3 / REM, EEG bands (Hz), muscle atonia, neurotransmitters (GABA, ACh, orexin/hypocretin, norepinephrine, serotonin, dopamine, histamine, melatonin, glutamate, glycine)
- Measurable or modelable signals (heart rate, tone, tremor, apnea-like patterns as physiological descriptions — never as diagnosis)

## NEVER use
- Psychoanalysis, Freud, Jung, archetypes, collective unconscious
- Mysticism, spirituality-as-explanation, astral / prophetic framing
- Dream dictionaries or “symbol X means Y”
- Vague “your subconscious is telling you…” language
- Medical diagnosis claims or treatment advice

## Page / matrix copy rules
- Frame events as physiological state transitions, not meanings.
- Prefer concrete markers: atonia preserved/failed, band-limited EEG, transmitter tone shifts.
- Include a non-diagnosis disclaimer where health-adjacent symptoms appear.
- Every somatic PSEO page needs a hard CTA to Decode (`/#decode`) for neurobiological dream analysis — not a tiny footer-only link.
- Target scale for PSEO: ~300 strong symptom × somatic-marker × phase pages (see `oneirox-pseo-somatic.mdc`).
